1. run npm init. A json file will be created
2. npm install node-sass --save-dev
   OR
   npm install -g node-sass

3 File structure of project should be like this :

   name(folder)
     css(folder)
     saas(folder)
     index.html
     package.json

4. Open package.json and edit script like following   :

{
  "name": "natoure",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "nature project",
  "main": "index.js",
  "scripts": {
  "saas": "node-sass --watch saas/main.scss -o css"
  },
  "author": "vikash",
  "license": "ISC"
}

5. now  "npm run saas"
6.It will generate the respected css file in css folder

           OR
           Install Ruby

Arguments  ->       --no-cache --update $FileName$:$FileNameWithoutExtension$.css
Output  ->          $FileNameWithoutExtension$.css:$FileNameWithoutExtension$.css.map
Program ->          C:\Ruby26-x64\bin\scss




